Affiliation: Laboratoire de Recherche en Informatique, CNRS, Universite de Paris-Sud,  Dept. of Computer Science, University of Bonn, 53117 Bonn, and International Computer Science Institute, Berkeley, California,  
Pubnum: TR-97-059  
Email: Email: lalo@lri.lri.fr  Email: marek@cs.bonn.edu  
Date: December 1997  
Abstract: We give the first polynomial time approximability characterization of dense weighted instances of MAX-CUT, and some other dense weighted N P-hard problems in terms of their empirical weight distributions. This gives also the first almost sharp characterization of inapproximability of unweighted 0,1 MAX-BISECTION instances in terms of their density parameter only. 
